The need for speed The Run is fought across America.
Revision
Originally a problem-free race turns into a set of stupid mistakes by people who have nothing to do with a routine morning commute to work.
It fulfills everyone’s ambition to a certain extent, but it’s useless if no one wants to do something more.
The new part subtitled The Run produced great expectations before its release.
He promised to take a new direction with the already aged Need for Speed racing series and release some sort of game from the playable parts that would not only count with points.
So we were curious about the added passages where the main hero gets out of his car and does what he wants.
As is already done in the NFS series, the result is completely different from what was expected.
These are potentially arcade racing games but the whole shoots down because of a few unnecessary mistakes that have already existed for several years.
These are not really mistakes but rather the expression of an incomprehensible idleness on the part of the developers.
The adventure begins very well.
You are caught up in the adventure whose main hero Jack has character problems and to fix them starts to participate in illegal races across America.
You sit behind the wheel on the West Coast in San Francisco and your mission is to arrive first in New York.
The idea has interesting elements.
The route is divided into ten stages and then into more than 50 races.
As a result, each race takes place on a different route and the stages planned in different environments that stand out quite well from each other and are interesting.
The player does not feel for a moment that the game offers him something identical.
Some environments are also pretty nice even if the graphic technical level is of the same type as the previous series.
This is not the end of the world.
But driving through the desert, in autumn landscapes or in highly snowy mountains is very visually pleasing.
The events are in addition from time to time embellished with an atypical element.
For example, in the desert you find yourself in a sandstorm that significantly decreases your visibility.
Then in the mountains you have to be careful that an avalanche does not fall on you.
Next to this the different races are well arranged one behind the other.
There are only a few, but that is enough.
There are moments you strive to surpass the requested number of opponents (as in a classic race) then you run against the clock (classic duel with the stopwatch) and then still awaits you another duel with an opponent.
From time to time you also have the police coming into the game and trying to make the situation difficult for you.
The novelty is the out-of-vehicle passages.
It’s more of an interactive animation when most of the time Jack runs away in front of someone and you have to help him by tapping the right button at the right time.
Nothing complicated.
What is surprising is that there are fewer moments of this type than what you expect (to be concrete there are only three).
As a result, this is good because this element is not likely to interfere and is placed, in the context described above, in the elements that enhance the game.
The driving model is in the tradition of previous games.
This means that at present there is nothing extraordinary, but it cannot be said to be negative.
As for the realistic simulation you will have to go elsewhere.
But although one can find better in the competition the driving model goes very well with the type of design of the races.
So everything is ok.
Problems begin to appear after a while.
At the difference of the driving model, that of the collisions is not yet at the point.
We don’t expect this game to have complicated deformation and collisions, but when you don’t have, during a collision with any object, the slightest idea of how your car behaves, it’s not completely good.
During tight overtaking you sometimes touch each other slightly but otherwise your car goes in crazy aerobatic.
Or is it crumbling.
Thanks to the reboot system this is not really a problem but it really annoys you.
The reboot is done in such a way that when you broke your face or went out in the scenery the game takes you back to the moment of the last point on the route.
But you only have 5 restarts.
When you have used the 5 restarts you must start the game again from the beginning.
So it’s more of a tool, in case something doesn’t go right, than something you can really rely on.
Sometimes restarts do not help and you have to find the solution by remembering the piece of route in question.
The big catch of this game is that the same actions are found in the same places.
For example, there are certain turns that must be passed in a certain way otherwise it does not pass.
Otherwise you encounter on a given place "civil" vehicles always in the same configuration as you arrived first, fifth, 5 seconds in advance or a minute late.
What makes you angry are the situations when you see the opponent pass easily between two cars coming in the opposite direction and when you arrive, you must either put yourself aside and conturn them or brake.
It does not matter if you go to meet him because it is "calculated" in such a way that for the given situation it always arrives very close to your nose.
Opponents have other advantages.
Throughout the game, you arrive in certain places, again without worrying about time, and you always have the same opponent that precedes you in the same place.
This gets the most upset at the end of the game when you ride on a long bridge in the opposite direction.
The opponent must pass in front of you at all costs.
When it passes in front of you it hides the view of other vehicles in the opposite direction and you collide a good number of times.
One can understand that the goal of this game is to do something captivating and full of adrenaline, but it is clear that you get bored quickly.
And it's a shame because through a simple driving model the game is interesting and places with so much action that you don't have time to follow everything that's going on.
And it doesn't matter if it's because of the concept of 50 unique routes, that the order of the races is such that there's no chance of getting bored or anything else.
The original idea is to change cars during races.
You have to pay attention to the gas pumps on the routes because you can change cars there however most of the time the one you have is enough for you.
Cars are divided into three categories.
Sports cars are ideal for cities, large American displacements for straight highways and super sports cars with exotic attires on highly technical drives for example on yaw roads in the mountains.
And the challenge mode, which are races in particular places that you know of adventure, goes very well with the main diet of the story.
You receive not only medals but also experience points that add to your profile that is common to challenges and adventure.
When you have reached the highest level of driver, different objects start to unlock:
It connects online with the Autolog function, which compares your results with those of other players and provides you with other functions in the community.
One of the hardest moves to understand is the situation of the last race of the adventure.
You arrive with your car in the subway tunnel (it looks like) where you drive in the dark on the tracks (it looks like).
Your speedometer tells you between 150 and 200 km/hour (a priori) and behind you comes a subway train that sends you the car directly to the scrap.
At the writing we had a discussion for a few days about whether someone really thought when creating this game or if the authors really take us for fools.
The technical part of the game is not extra, but the visual part is generally nice and in some cases really great.
What bothers is that in more extreme situations, the imagery does not hold the level and in some cases tragically.
This especially concerns accidents with a large number of participants when fluid imaging is no longer useful to you.
The sound part is good and the track is your choice.
In order to please as many people as possible and especially the younger audience, a new sound track has been created in the "I mix everything" style, but we can expect that no one will buy the game for music.
General Impression of Need for Speed: The Run is therefore really confusing.
If the game didn’t have these stupid mistakes we could safely say that this is the best NFS production in recent years.
But this game feels like it’s not finished.
The fun is really good but be prepared for mistakes to hit you in the eye with the strength of an aerodrome reflector.
Velvet students in concert with the choirs of Charles University
The Festa Academica festival offers for the third time festivities that link International Student Day with the anniversary of the Velvet Revolution with a musical part.
During the festival there are 20 choirs from upper and secondary schools.
The highlight of the festival is two concerts organized on November 17.
"Charles University has an important part in this festival."
"Among the choirs there is the Choir of the Faculty of Pedagogy and Humanities, in the committee of the festival is the rector Vaclav Hampl," says the leader of the organizing team Jakub Calou.
The highlight of the festival is the concert of the Choir of high schools and secondary classes which takes place with free entry on November 17 from 2 pm on the space located in front of the National Technical Library in Dejvice.
On the program is the composition of the well-known Czech jazzman Karel Ruzicka, Celebration Jazz mass.
In the evening takes place the concert "Students of velvet" in the premises of the National House in Vinohrady during which the choirs of the higher schools as well as that of Charles University are performed.
The Festa Academica aims not only to celebrate International Student Day with dignity and remember the 22nd anniversary of the Velvet Revolution, but also to present to the public choir music of the highest level and develop the creative cooperation of young people.
The main organizer is the Union of Czech Chorus in cooperation with Jan Kepler High School.
All the action is under the aegis of Bohuslav Svoboda, Mayor of Prague and Vaclav Hampl, Rector of Charles University.
The festival takes place from 16 to 20 November in Prague and Pardubice.
The program offers in addition to high-level concerts, msicales meetings, student happening and other activities.
Interested parties will find all the information on the Internet pages of the festival www.festaacademica.cz.
Vicenova, Ambassador to the European Union:
Czechs behave like negativists and eurosceptics
"The Lisbon Treaty has radically eliminated the balance between the institutions"
“I didn’t expect such a tough war.”
“It will last 5.6 years before the situation calms down and all the players get used to their new role,” said Milena Vicenova, the Czech ambassador to the European Union.
When she was able to describe the different bodies of the EU and their relations in such a comprehensible and visible way, to the point that a large number of lecturers from Charles University's Faculty of Law might envy her, she showed how seriously she takes her "understandable and openly about Europe" motto.
Vicenova paid tribute to the work of Herman Van Rompuye, the new Permanent President of the European Council.
"From the beginning there were criticisms that he's bland, that he's a cudgel, that he can't take on any mission and I have to say that he took everyone's breath away because he plays his part perfectly."
"He is a man who knows how to listen to 27 member states, communicate well with them and has a clear vision of where Europe should go."
She explained the new post of the High Representative for Foreign Affairs and Defence Policy as part of an answer to the question: "Who is who in the European Union?" "What telephone number should I call?", thus as an important step towards the uniqueness and greater readability of the Union's policy vis-à-vis states, such as China or India.
No one wants to ban us from our syrecky (cooked cheese that smells very strong)
Mrs Vicenova also mentioned the agenda that the European Council has lived, is living and will live in the near future.
She called the Czech presidency a success two years ago.
The Czechs have solved the rising financial crisis, the gas crisis or have organized a Summit for an Eastern Partnership.
She described the fall of the government as very negative and damaged the image of the Czech Republic.
The Czech representation in the EU is very busy at the moment.
In the words of the Ambassador, "activity has been in full swing" not only for the Presidency but also for the financial crisis that continues to be resolved even now.
We must also approve the Union's new seven-year budget, which is becoming very complicated because of the current economic situation.
As it seems that the budget will be slim and with a view to savings, which branch will have priority, which countries will be helped the most, the least, everything is to be resolved in the context of future negotiations.
The Ambassador recalled her slogans with which she arrived in Brussels "For an understandable Europe".
“I really don’t like abbreviations, foreign words, jargons that no one understands.
As the citizen must understand that it is true that in Brussels no one makes round or crooked pickles, bananas that are different in size or that no one has forbidden us to make syrecky.
She wants to make better use of the EU environment and see more Czechs in the European institutions.
A multi-speed Europe awaits us
According to the Ambassador, the Czechs have a reputation for being Eurosceptics and people who only see things in their negative aspect more than positively.
Moreover, she is sorry to see such a small Czech representation in the European institutions.
According to her, the fault is due to several factors, such as the timidity of our candidates, their inability to write a cover letter and weak support from the Czech side.
In addition to a successful Czech Presidency, she then highlighted the strength and cooperation of the Visegrad Group.
“Believe me, when the Pole, the Magyar, the Slovak come to me, this Frenchman says to me: ‘Hey, what are you doing there, what is this Visegrad group still doing?’ and he’s not at all happy.”
According to Ms Vicenova, in the near future new tough fiscal policy rules await the member countries.
It is the concept of a two-speed, if not multi-speed, Europe that prevails rather than a "new European Federation".
“We have countries in the euro zone and others outside the zone.”
“We have the Schengen area, we also have the Institute for Enhanced Cooperation.”
In the first place, it was said that the countries that want it and those that don’t want to stay in their corner are cooperating with each other.”
“There will be a lot of institutes of this type and there will be a really two-speed Europe,” Vicenova said.
From this point of view it also appreciated the mission of the Czech Republic and Herman Van Rompuye to determine the bases according to which all the topics having an impact on the EU should be discussed among all the members of the EU and not only the members of the eurozone.
History of a brand:
IBM Innovator Begins Second Century of Its Existence
If someone were to look for the term that most closely expresses the IBM strategy, the closest would be “the long term.”
For a large audience IBM is the symbol of the technological revolution, is a firm felt as very current and yet since its creation it has been a hundred years.
The foundation for this long-term strategy was laid by the firm’s first leader, visionary Thomas J. Watson Sr.
He left the slogan that many global problems can be solved if people are willing to think.
Its slogan "PENSE'!" became the imprint around which the life of a future giant will develop (and also the title of the internal magazine that IBM began to publish in 1935).
This was the basis of Watson's carefully crafted corporate culture.
For us IBM means a long-term thought of continuous movements directed towards the future.
IBM survived a hundred years because it always remained true to its core values and yet was not afraid to change all the others around it.
This has enabled us in our first century to transform technology, business and society.
We hope that in the second century we will reach even more" dilapidated for the anniversary the current director of the firm Samuel J. Palmisano.
A well-prepared system
Watson, in the 1930s, began to care for his employees like Bata in the Czech Republic - IBM people were the only ones among the first American employees to have paid vacations, employer-paid insurance plus a stylish employee uniform and a well-developed system of rewards for inventors and marketers.
Similarly, IBM has a well-developed system of customer relationships.
The company was at first brilliant at discovering talent – as one of the first firms to have abolished all forms of discrimination and thus had a choice.
The current plan is completely in the spirit of anti-discrimination strategy since it will be a woman - Virginia Rometty - who should replace Palmisano at the head of IBM.
She has been with IBM for thirty years and currently serves as Head of Sales, Marketing and Strategy.
IBM in recent years has been doing what is known as jamy, online brain-storming from which many future strategies and innovations have emerged.
No wonder he has a lot of ideas - in the firm there are nearly 500,000 people working.
