This is an excerpt from the conversation, the full transcript of which can be found in La Nacion on the Internet.
For his Costa Rican followers, the fact that Pearl Jam will perform in Costa Rica is a dream come true. Are you aware of what your fans are experiencing?
Going to Costa Rica is a dream that has come true for us too.
This is our second time in South and Central America and so far it has been grandiose.
I spent in Costa Rica only once the holidays; it is such a beautiful country and I think we will be able to spend a few days there.
We are excited to bring our music there.
I ask you, because there is a kind of devotion to the band, the fans live with intensity on the previous days.
What is your message to your most ardent followers?
Thank you for staying with us for all these years.
It took 21 years for us to get to Costa Rica; thank you for waiting so long and we are sorry that so much time had to pass until this concert.
Some people already say that his concert is the biggest show of the year.
Does this add some pressure to your visit?
Some of the biggest shows we’ve offered over the past 21 years have taken place in the last couple of weeks.
We offered a two gigantic shows in Sao Paolo and we hope it put us in shape for this concert in Costa Rica.
We are really looking forward to performing there.
We love this country, we love surfing and the jungle; for both things, Costa Rica is one of the best countries in the world.
How did you discover Costa Rica and its waves for surfing?
We have a lot of surfing friends and I have a very good friend who lives in Tamarindo and the waves are amazing there.
My friends always went surfing in Costa Rica and Nicaragua, next to Mexico, are great places to go surfing; that's how we learned it, through the people who love surfing.
Seeing the tour, you were offered huge shows, with a lot of songs.
What did you plan for your presentation in Costa Rica?
Since we have never happened there, we have no restrictions on what we can do.
We will try to make the best show possible, with a wide variety of songs; we will try to perform two songs from each album and offer our fans a good and diverse repertoire.
You never repeat the directory.
What do you owe it to?
I think it’s partly because we have nine records and we can perform more than 120 songs and everyone likes different songs, which is why it’s very difficult to choose which songs to perform each night.
When we have two or three songs in the repertoire that we haven’t performed in a very long time, it helps us stay focused and surprises us because it reminds us of why we loved those songs and may have forgotten about them.
It makes the show more interesting for us and therefore I think it also becomes more interesting for people.
With this tour, you celebrate 20 years of trajectory.
Looking back, is it hard to believe everything you’ve achieved?
Yes, absolutely.
