The Secretariat of Communications and Transport (SCT) informed that the results highlighted on the accident in which lost his life the Secretary of Government, Francisco Blake Mora and other seven people, indicate that the helicopter shocked directly against the ground in complete structural integrity, without the pilot being able to try a forced landing.
