During the field work, parts of the aircraft were found at a height of 9 thousand 200 feet above average sea level, the ground had a slope that went from seven degrees to 30 degrees of inclination.
The photographs show the sequence in which he possibly disarticulated along his journey.
The information provides evidence that suggests the helicopter may have had multiple impacts with the ground.
